name: Symbol.Symbol
description: The Symbol() constructor returns a value of type symbol, but is incomplete as a constructor because it does not support the syntax "new Symbol()" and it is not intended to be subclassed. It may be used as the value of an extends clause of a class definition but a super call to it will cause an exception.
